t=\r\nhe varna of one&#39;s father, as that is what one is exposed to in childhood. H=\r\nowever, as one&#39;s vasana (mental conditioning) blooms, one would get one&#39;s o=\r\nwn varna. One born a Shudra like Valmiki, for example, can later turn into =\r\na Braahmana and become a Maharshi. One born a Kshatriya like Viswamitra, fo=\r\nr example, can later turn into a Brahmana and become a Maharshi.\n\nIn the ol=\r\nd days, there were true Brahmanas, who would only be interested in knowledg=\r\ne and spiritual progress and not caring about power, influence, money, plea=\r\nsures etc. Such Brahmanas became quite pure and accumulated enough spiritua=\r\nl energy through continuous sadhana over years and were capable of performi=\r\nng very effective poojas for people.\n\nToday, people who have spiritual pote=\r\nntial may be born in non-Brahmana families and not allowed to develop fully=\r\n due to the rigid caste structures. Some people born in Brahmana families m=\r\nay also end up getting into modern careers and not developing fully as Brah=\r\nmanas. Some people may be born in Brahmana families with Kshatriya/Vaisya/S=\r\nhudra tendencies and may end up becoming priests who are interested in powe=\r\nr, authority and control over others, money and physical pleasures. Those p=\r\nriests who only care about knowledge and spiritual progress (i.e. true Brah=\r\nmanas) are very rare. As a result, Brahmanas who have done genuine sadhana =\r\nand accumulated a good amount of spiritual energy are so few.\n\n* * *\n\nIf on=\r\ne has one million dollars in one&#39;s bank account, a check given by one for t=\r\nhousand dollars is meaningful. If one&#39;s bank account is empty, what good is=\r\n a thousand dollar check given by one? It will bounce. Similarly, poojas do=\r\nne and blessings given by a priest without enough spiritual energy cannot b=\r\nring one any benefits.\n\nOne important note: The power is not in a combinati=\r\non of syllables (mantra) or a sequence of physical actions (ritual). The po=\r\nwer is in the MIND that FOCUSES on a combination of syllables (mantra) or a=\r\n sequence of physical actions (ritual). Energy is generated when mind overc=\r\nomes its tendency to wander and instead focuses on one thing. Different man=\r\ntras and rituals as the focus points may generate different kinds of energy=\r\n, but the key is focus. Without it, no mantra or ritual produces anything. =\r\nFocus comes with a lot of practice. Most priests are just engaging in casua=\r\nl practice when they go and do poojas. In the old days, priests did intense=\r\n sadhana and brought that energy to the table when they did rituals at the =\r\nhouses of people or in temples.\n\nI did see priests who have done good sadha=\r\nna, purified themselves and carry some spiritual energy. But those are gett=\r\ning rarer and rarer now-a-days. One can most certainly not bank on finding =\r\nsuch a priest.\n\n* * *\n\nGiven this, one is better off not depending on the p=\r\nriest/Brahmana class for remedies. BTW, I have nothing against the &quot;Brahman=\r\na by birth&quot; class, having been born in an orthodox Brahmana family myself. =\r\nI have neither love nor hatred for the &quot;Brahmana by birth&quot; class. My only w=\r\nish is that more people - from any birth caste - develop into true Brahmana=\r\ns.\n\nInstead of a Brahmana-by-birth who is possibly proud of his skills and =\r\nthinking about money and possibly not identifying with your trouble, you ca=\r\nn do the mantra/ritual yourself. Atleast your identification with the troub=\r\nle and your desire to solve the problem will be better than the priest. If =\r\nyou manage to generate enough focus after practice, the mantra/ritual may a=\r\nctually produce some result. There is no harm in trying.\n\n* * *\n\nMany peopl=\r\ne think that poojas to gods are a serious matter and only a trained priest =\r\nshould do them. The procedures have evolved to become quite complicated ove=\r\nr the time too!\n\nHowever, complexity of rituals should never be a deterrent=\r\n. Suppose rules dictate that you MUST eat 2000 calories everyday, 40 grams =\r\nof protein, so many grams of vitamin A etc. Suppose you have no access to s=\r\nuch balanced food. Will you starve yourself until you find a balanced meal =\r\nor will you manage with whatever you have? If you just have a bowl of dal (=\r\nlentil soup) and rice, you will simply eat it. You atleast get some energy.=\r\n\n\nSimilarly, if you do not know the &quot;perfect way&quot; to do a mantra/ritual, yo=\r\nu need not wait till you know the perfect way. You can start with what you =\r\nknow. It will only give you energy.\n\n* * *\n\nThe fear to do rituals without =\r\n&quot;perfect knowledge&quot; stems from the notion that some mantras/rituals can be =\r\ndangerous. That notion is not totally baseless, but it is irrelevant today.=\r\n\n\nIt is possible to focus the mind on some mantras and rituals and get spec=\r\nific results. When used by someone with a high level of spiritual energy, s=\r\nome mantras and rituals may work very fast and give specific powerful resul=\r\nts. However, Nature has purposely hidden (almost) such things in this age.\n=\r\n\nI will give an analogy. A machine gun and a stick can be used to attack en=\r\nemies. Stick is safe to use, but, one using a machine gun needs to be very =\r\ncareful. One needs to learn well, practice well and then use it, lest one s=\r\nhould hurt oneself by accident.\n\nHowever, suppose the house lord purposely =\r\nremoved ammunition from the machine gun. Then it is used just like a stick =\r\nand not risky. Instead of waiting for perfect instructions on how to use th=\r\ne machine gun, just take it and start beating your enemies with it.\n\n&quot;Ammun=\r\nition&quot; has purposely been removed from most targeted mantras and rituals (m=\r\nachine guns) in this age. Instead of waiting for perfect knowledge, one can=\r\n start using them right away.\n\nA lot of technicalities related to mantras a=\r\nnd rituals are irrelevant today. Mantras and rituals are to be taken up wit=\r\nh faith, devotion and surrender to god. Whatever technicalities one can rea=\r\nlistically follow should be followed and emphasis should be placed on devot=\r\nion and surrender. If one keeps doing sadhana, eventually one&#39;s devotion an=\r\nd focus will improve and, for all you know, a result may come.\n\nGiven that =\r\nwe do not have perfect focus and surrender, we cannot expect specific resul=\r\nts to come in specific counts of recitation. So we should just do the best =\r\njob we can and leave the result to god, who decides when and what result sh=\r\nould be given.\n\nBottomline is that no effort is wasted in the end. Every si=\r\nncere effort generates some fruit or the other, sometime or the other!!!\n\n*=\r\n * *\n\nDifferent mantras and rituals are like begging bowls of different sha=\r\npes. They matter only so much. Depending on what kind of a begging bowl you=\r\n use, you may be given different kind of alms. But it is important to start=\r\n begging with some begging bowl or the other, instead of spending years loo=\r\nking for the perfect begging bowl.\n\nInstead of waiting for astrologers with=\r\n half-baked or ill-conceived knowledge to tell you the perfect mantra or ri=\r\ntual, do what your heart tells you or what your guru (or an elder you respe=\r\nct) tells you. Mantras like Gayatri mantra, Shiva panchakshari mantra, Vish=\r\nnu sahasranaama stotra, Ganapathi atharva seersha, Hanuman chalisa, Bheemar=\r\nupi Hanuman stotra, Vishnu&#39;s shadakshari/ashtakshari/dwadasakshari mantra, =\r\nVenkateswara&#39;s ashtakshari/dwadasakshari mantra, hare krishna mantra, Chand=\r\nipath (Durga saptashati), Durga saptashloki, Lalita sahasranaama stotra, Vy=\r\nasa&#39;s navagraha stotra, Aditya Hridayam, Lakshmi ashtottarashatanaama stotr=\r\na etc are *generic* and can work for anyone for any purpose.\n\nDo not waste =\r\ntime looking for a perfect recommendation, perfect procedure, perfect muhur=\r\nta etc and just do some sadhana or the other with a sincere heart.\n\nYour ef=\r\nfort will not go waste. Your problem may be solved or you may overcome your=\r\n situation and stop worrying, or atleast your focus will improve.\n\n* * *\n\nI=\r\nn this context, I want to say a few words about homam, the sadhana of rishi=\r\ns.\n\nFire ritual is found in many ancient religions. Unlike the elements of =\r\nearth, water and air, fire is ever pure and it purifies whatever it comes i=\r\nn contact with. The Sanskrit name for fire is paavaka, i.e. purifier. Fire =\r\nis a living god that everyone has access to. Spending time worshipping god =\r\nthrough fire purifies one&#39;s subtle consciousness. Homam is far more effecti=\r\nve than most other sadhanas in improving one&#39;s focus, changing one&#39;s inner =\r\npersonality and removing material and spiritual obstacles. One need not tak=\r\ne my words for granted. One can try for oneself for a few months. The proof=\r\n of the pudding is in eating it.\n\nVedic seers (rishis) performed homam regu=\r\nlarly, for the benefit of the world. When composing the Jyotish masterpiece=\r\n &quot;Brihat Paaraasara Horaa Saastram&quot; just before the advent of Kali yuga, fo=\r\nr guidance to the people of Kali yuga, Maharshi Parasara recommended variou=\r\ns types of homam as remedial measures for various problems in the horoscope=\r\n. In fact, most remedies he recommended involve homam. Parasara asked to fo=\r\nllow whatever procedures one was taught for starting fire and did not focus=\r\n on the nitty gritty of homam. He only gave the main mantra to beused in ho=\r\nmam. Parasara&#39;s clear teachings set to rest the notion that some people hav=\r\ne, that homam is not for Kali yuga.\n\n* * *\n\nIn Bhagavad Gita, Sri Krishna s=\r\naid, &quot;yaGYaanaaM japayaGYo.asmi&quot;, i.e. I am japa among all sacrifices. Some=\r\n people use this line to suggest that japam (meditation) is superior to hom=\r\na/yajna. Let me put that in perspective.\n\nIn the line just above that line,=\r\n Sri Krishna also said, &quot;I am Om among all mantras&quot;. However, do we only me=\r\nditate with the supreme mantra &quot;Om&quot; and leave all other mantras?\n\nIf one sa=\r\nys that sitting on the pinnacle is the best part of climbing a mountain, it=\r\n does not mean that the process of climbing it using various kinds of gear =\r\nis useless. In fact, one needs that process to reach the pinnacle. Most can=\r\nnot reach the pinnacle directly.\n\nSimilarly, Om is the supreme of all mantr=\r\nas being the source of all, but reaching the source may require using sever=\r\nal mantras first to purify oneself. Meditating and absorbing consciousness =\r\nin the Supreme (japa) may be the supreme sacrifice, but it may require puri=\r\nfication and preparation by engaging in other kinds of sacrifices (hama/yaj=\r\nna).\n\nWhen one does homam or yajna, one is engaging in external actions and=\r\n one is unlikely to reach samadhi (absorbption in the Supreme). When a perf=\r\nectly purified person does japam (i.e. sits still and contemplates), one ma=\r\ny reach samadhi. However, to purify oneself, homam is far more effective.\n\n=\r\n* * *\n\nDetailed manuals giving short procedures for doing various types of =\r\nhomam by oneself are available on the website given below. You can use the =\r\nresources on that website to perform several kinds of short homam by yourse=\r\nlf.\n\nNow *hundreds* of people are performing homam by themselves either dai=\r\nly or weekly. Some people are also doing monthly.\n\nWhen Manish (my spiritua=\r\nl guru - a small write-up on him can be read in message 3481 of vedic-wisdo=\r\nm yahoogroup, i.e. http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom/message/3481)=\r\n told me that the Divine Mother appeared before him during Shata Chandi hom=\r\nam at a temple in Chennai in March 2006, directed him to spread a simplifie=\r\nd homam ritual around the world, and showed him that hundreds of thousands =\r\nof people would be performing regular homam in a few years, thus helping re=\r\nverse the decay of Dharma and Truth on earth, it seemed quite far-fetched t=\r\no my rational mind.\n\nHowever, just 4 years after the Mother&#39;s command, hund=\r\nreds of people are already performing regular homam. Though these are just =\r\nthe early days, the developments are amazing. Some of them are laymen who n=\r\never even lit a lamp and did not know how to do ANY pooja or ritual. It is =\r\na miracle that such people are doing a homam everyday, like the rishis and =\r\nBrahmanas of yore. I also know personally that some people doing homam for =\r\na couple of years are actually starting to experience things within and out=\r\nside and, more importantly, going through rapid internal transformation.\n\n*=\r\n * *\n\nI am neither a missionary nor a mercenary. I do not sell anything to =\r\nanyone, nor do I force anything on anyone. I just freely share what I know,=\r\n what I saw and what I am inspired to share. The rest is not in my hands.\n\n=\r\nI want to respectfully, humbly and lovingly invite those who have even an i=\r\nota of interest to check out the homam website! If one gets into the habit =\r\nof performing homam regularly, it has the great potential to transform one&#39;=\r\ns life, materially and spiritually..\n\nHomam website:\nhttp://www.VedicAstrol=\r\noger.org/homam\n\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n-----------------------------------=\r\n-----------------------\nFree Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotis=\r\nh Writings,\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpa=\r\nna:\nhttp://www.VedicAstrologer.org\nFilms that make a difference: http://Sar=\r\naswatiFilms.org\nSpirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\nJy=\r\notish writings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n-------------=\r\n---------------------------------------------\n\n\