e=\r\nople born in Brahmana families may also end up getting into modern careers =\r\nand not developing fully as Brahmanas. Some people may be born in Brahmana =\r\nfamilies with Kshatriya/Vaisya/Shudra tendencies and may end up becoming pr=\r\niests who are interested in power, authority and control over others, money=\r\n and physical pleasures. Those priests who only care about knowledge and sp=\r\niritual progress (i.e. true Brahmanas) are very rare. As a result, Brahmana=\r\ns who have done genuine sadhana and accumulated a good amount of spiritual =\r\nenergy are so few.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If one has one million dollars in on=\r\ne&#39;s bank account, a check given by one for thousand dollars is meaningful. =\r\nIf one&#39;s bank account is empty, what good is a thousand dollar check given =\r\nby one? It will bounce. Similarly, poojas done and blessings given by\n a pr=\r\niest without enough spiritual energy cannot bring one any benefits.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;=\r\nOne important note: The power is not in a combination of syllables (mantra)=\r\n or a sequence of physical actions (ritual). The power is in the MIND that =\r\nFOCUSES on a combination of syllables (mantra) or a sequence of physical ac=\r\ntions (ritual). Energy is generated when mind overcomes its tendency to wan=\r\nder and instead focuses on one thing. Different mantras and rituals as the =\r\nfocus points may generate different kinds of energy, but the key is focus. =\r\nWithout it, no mantra or ritual produces anything. Focus comes with a lot o=\r\nf practice. Most priests are just engaging in casual practice when they go =\r\nand do poojas. In the old days, priests did intense sadhana and brought tha=\r\nt energy to the table when they did rituals at the houses of people or in t=\r\nemples.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;I did see priests who have done good sadhana, purified thems=\r\nelves and carry some spiritual energy. But those are getting\n rarer and rar=\r\ner now-a-days. One can most certainly not bank on finding such a priest.&lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Given this, one is better off not depending on the priest=\r\n/Brahmana class for remedies. BTW, I have nothing against the &quot;Brahmana by =\r\nbirth&quot; class, having been born in an orthodox Brahmana family myself. I hav=\r\ne neither love nor hatred for the &quot;Brahmana by birth&quot; class. My only wish i=\r\ns that more people - from any birth caste - develop into true Brahmanas.&lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Instead of a Brahmana-by-birth who is possibly proud of his skills and=\r\n thinking about money and possibly not identifying with your trouble, you c=\r\nan do the mantra/ritual yourself. Atleast your identification with the trou=\r\nble and your desire to solve the problem will be better than the priest. If=\r\n you manage to generate enough focus after practice, the mantra/ritual may =\r\nactually produce some result. There is no harm in trying.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;Many people think that poojas to gods are a serious\n matter and only a t=\r\nrained priest should do them. The procedures have evolved to become quite c=\r\nomplicated over the time too!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;However, complexity of rituals should =\r\nnever be a deterrent. Suppose rules dictate that you MUST eat 2000 calories=\r\n everyday, 40 grams of protein, so many grams of vitamin A etc. Suppose you=\r\n have no access to such balanced food. Will you starve yourself until you f=\r\nind a balanced meal or will you manage with whatever you have? If you just =\r\nhave a bowl of dal (lentil soup) and rice, you will simply eat it. You atle=\r\nast get some energy.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Similarly, if you do not know the &quot;perfect way&quot;=\r\n to do a mantra/ritual, you need not wait till you know the perfect way. Yo=\r\nu can start with what you know. It will only give you energy.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The fear to do rituals without &quot;perfect knowledge&quot; stems from the no=\r\ntion that some mantras/rituals can be dangerous. That notion is not totally=\r\n baseless, but it is irrelevant today.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;It\n is possible to focus the =\r\nmind on some mantras and rituals and get specific results. When used by som=\r\neone with a high level of spiritual energy, some mantras and rituals may wo=\r\nrk very fast and give specific powerful results. However, Nature has purpos=\r\nely hidden (almost) such things in this age.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;I will give an analogy.=\r\n A machine gun and a stick can be used to attack enemies. Stick is safe to =\r\nuse, but, one using a machine gun needs to be very careful. One needs to le=\r\narn well, practice well and then use it, lest one should hurt oneself by ac=\r\ncident.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;However, suppose the house lord purposely removed ammunition=\r\n from the machine gun. Then it is used just like a stick and not risky. Ins=\r\ntead of waiting for perfect instructions on how to use the machine gun, jus=\r\nt take it and start beating your enemies with it.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&quot;Ammunition&quot; has p=\r\nurposely been removed from most targeted mantras and rituals (machine guns)=\r\n in this age. Instead of waiting for\n perfect knowledge, one can start usin=\r\ng them right away.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;A lot of technicalities related to mantras and ri=\r\ntuals are irrelevant today. Mantras and rituals are to be taken up with fai=\r\nth, devotion and surrender to god. Whatever technicalities one can realisti=\r\ncally follow should be followed and emphasis should be placed on devotion a=\r\nnd surrender. If one keeps doing sadhana, eventually one&#39;s devotion and foc=\r\nus will improve and, for all you know, a result may come.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Given that=\r\n we do not have perfect focus and surrender, we cannot expect specific resu=\r\nlts to come in specific counts of recitation. So we should just do the best=\r\n job we can and leave the result to god, who decides when and what result s=\r\nhould be given.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Bottomline is that no effort is wasted in the end. E=\r\nvery sincere effort generates some fruit or the other, sometime or the othe=\r\nr!!!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Different mantras and rituals are like begging bow=\r\nls of different shapes. They\n matter only so much. Depending on what kind o=\r\nf a begging bowl you use, you may be given different kind of alms. But it i=\r\ns important to start begging with some begging bowl or the other, instead o=\r\nf spending years looking for the perfect begging bowl.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Instead of wa=\r\niting for astrologers with half-baked or ill-conceived knowledge to tell yo=\r\nu the perfect mantra or ritual, do what your heart tells you or what your g=\r\nuru (or an elder you respect) tells you. Mantras like Gayatri mantra, Shiva=\r\n panchakshari mantra, Vishnu sahasranaama stotra, Ganapathi atharva seersha=\r\n, Hanuman chalisa, Bheemarupi Hanuman stotra, Vishnu&#39;s shadakshari/ashtaksh=\r\nari/dwadasakshari mantra, Venkateswara&#39;s ashtakshari/dwadasakshari mantra, =\r\nhare krishna mantra, Chandipath (Durga saptashati), Durga saptashloki, Lali=\r\nta sahasranaama stotra, Vyasa&#39;s navagraha stotra, Aditya Hridayam, Lakshmi =\r\nashtottarashatanaama stotra etc are *generic* and can work for anyone for a=\r\nny purpose.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Do\n not waste time looking for a perfect recommendation,=\r\n perfect procedure, perfect muhurta etc and just do some sadhana or the oth=\r\ner with a sincere heart.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Your effort will not go waste. Your problem=\r\n may be solved or you may overcome your situation and stop worrying, or atl=\r\neast your focus will improve.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In this context, I want t=\r\no say a few words about homam, the sadhana of rishis.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Fire ritual is=\r\n found in many ancient religions. Unlike the elements of earth, water and a=\r\nir, fire is ever pure and it purifies whatever it comes in contact with. Th=\r\ne Sanskrit name for fire is paavaka, i.e. purifier. Fire is a living god th=\r\nat everyone has access to. Spending time worshipping god through fire purif=\r\nies one&#39;s subtle consciousness. Homam is far more effective than most other=\r\n sadhanas in improving one&#39;s focus, changing one&#39;s inner personality and re=\r\nmoving material and spiritual obstacles. One need not take my words for gra=\r\nnted. One can\n try for oneself for a few months. The proof of the pudding i=\r\ns in eating it.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Vedic seers (rishis) performed homam regularly, for =\r\nthe benefit of the world. When composing the Jyotish masterpiece &quot;Brihat Pa=\r\naraasara Horaa Saastram&quot; just before the advent of Kali yuga, for guidance =\r\nto the people of Kali yuga, Maharshi Parasara recommended various types of =\r\nhomam as remedial measures for various problems in the horoscope. In fact, =\r\nmost remedies he recommended involve homam. Parasara asked to follow whatev=\r\ner procedures one was taught for starting fire and did not focus on the nit=\r\nty gritty of homam. He only gave the main mantra to beused in homam. Parasa=\r\nra&#39;s clear teachings set to rest the notion that some people have, that hom=\r\nam is not for Kali yuga.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In Bhagavad Gita, Sri Krishna =\r\nsaid, &quot;yaGYaanaaM japayaGYo.asmi&quot;, i.e. I am japa among all sacrifices. Som=\r\ne people use this line to suggest that japam (meditation) is superior to\n h=\r\noma/yajna. Let me put that in perspective.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In the line just above th=\r\nat line, Sri Krishna also said, &quot;I am Om among all mantras&quot;. However, do we=\r\n only meditate with the supreme mantra &quot;Om&quot; and leave all other mantras?&lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If one says that sitting on the pinnacle is the best part of climbing =\r\na mountain, it does not mean that the process of climbing it using various =\r\nkinds of gear is useless. In fact, one needs that process to reach the pinn=\r\nacle. Most cannot reach the pinnacle directly.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Similarly, Om is the =\r\nsupreme of all mantras being the source of all, but reaching the source may=\r\n require using several mantras first to purify oneself. Meditating and abso=\r\nrbing consciousness in the Supreme (japa) may be the supreme sacrifice, but=\r\n it may require purification and preparation by engaging in other kinds of =\r\nsacrifices (hama/yajna).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When one does homam or yajna, one is engagi=\r\nng in external actions and one is unlikely to reach samadhi\n (absorbption i=\r\nn the Supreme). When a perfectly purified person does japam (i.e. sits stil=\r\nl and contemplates), one may reach samadhi. However, to purify oneself, hom=\r\nam is far more effective.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Detailed manuals giving short=\r\n procedures for doing various types of homam by oneself are available on th=\r\ne website given below. You can use the resources on that website to perform=\r\n several kinds of short homam by yourself.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Now *hundreds* of people =\r\nare performing homam by themselves either daily or weekly. Some people are =\r\nalso doing monthly.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When Manish (my spiritual guru - a small write-u=\r\np on him can be read in message 3481 of vedic-wisdom yahoogroup, i.e. &lt;A hr=\r\nef=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom/message/3481&quot; target=3D_bl=\r\nank rel=3Dnofollow&gt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom/message/3481&lt;=\r\n/A&gt;) told me that the Divine Mother appeared before him during Shata Chandi=\r\n homam at a temple in Chennai in March 2006, directed him\n to spread a simp=\r\nlified homam ritual around the world, and showed him that hundreds of thous=\r\nands of people would be performing regular homam in a few years, thus helpi=\r\nng 